How to compile fftw
-------------------

On MacOS:
Download source code:
wget http://www.fftw.org/fftw-3.3.6-pl2.tar.gz
tar -xvzf fftw-3.3.6-pl2.tar.gz
cd fftw-3.3.6-pl2
Slicer targets OS 10.6, so we do the same here:
CFLAGS="-mmacosx-version-min=10.6" ./configure --enable-shared --enable-static=no --enable-threads --prefix `pwd`/fftw-install
make -j8
make install
tar -cvzf fftw-3.3.6-pl2_macOS_10.6.tar.gz fftw-install

Upload file 

NOTES
-----

Once compiled on MacOS, shape4d will not run without changing the paths/names in fftw3.3.dylib
It is not a problem as the goal is to package it as an extension for Slicer and Slicer packaging system modifies the library
paths.
To manually make the tool work on MacOS, use:
install_name_tool -change /Users/kitware/Dashboards/Francois/fftw-3.3.6-pl2/fftw-install/lib/libfftw3.3.dylib @executable_path/libfftw3.3.dylib shape4d
Or
install_name_tool -id libfftw3.3.dylib libfftw3.3.dylib
